Calculated Leontief Inverse Matrix[Source ISIC Code, Target ISIC Code] :EXCEPT:  [Industry Category ISIC Code\
		,Target ISIC Code
]=
	DLIM Domestic Leontief Inverse Matrix[Source ISIC Code,Target ISIC Code] ~~|
Calculated Leontief Inverse Matrix[Industry Category ISIC Code,Target ISIC Code]=
	DLIM Domestic Leontief Inverse Matrix[Industry Category ISIC Code,Target ISIC Code]
	* (1 - Fraction of Imports Shifted to In Region Suppliers After Import Substitution[\
		Industry Category])
	+
	TLIM Total Leontief Inverse Matrix[Industry Category ISIC Code,Target ISIC Code]
	* Fraction of Imports Shifted to In Region Suppliers After Import Substitution[Industry Category\
		]
	~	Dmnl
	~	Here, the "source" ISIC code is the supplying industry and the "target" \
		ISIC code is the industry being supplied.  Therefore, to shift an \
		industry's outputs to in-region suppliers, we need to affect the "source" \
		industry.  The outputs are then shifted for all buyers of that industry's \
		outputs (i.e. for all "target" industries).
	|

Calculated Leontief Inverse Matrix Excluding Direct Impacts[Source ISIC Code,Target ISIC Code\
		]=
	Calculated Leontief Inverse Matrix[Source ISIC Code,Target ISIC Code]
	- Identity Matrix for ISIC Codes[Source ISIC Code,Target ISIC Code]
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Capacity Construction Subsidies Paid[Electricity Source]=
	New and Retrofit Generation Capacity[Electricity Source]
	* Subsidy per Unit Electricity Capacity Built[Electricity Source]
	
	+ New Hybrid Grid Battery Storage Capacity[Electricity Source]
	* Subsidy per Unit Grid Battery Capacity Deployed
	~	$
	~		|

Capacity Market Costs for Diurnal Storage=
	(SUM
	  (Capacity Market Price for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability by Optimization Pass[\
		last pass!]
	  )
	  * (1 - Battery Storage Usage Factor Discount in Binding Peak Hour)
	  *This Year Grid Battery Storage Capacity excluding Hybrid Batteries in MW
	)
	
	*ESTRTE Grid Battery Round Trip Efficiency
	*Days per Year
	* One Day
	~	$
	~		|

Capacity Market Optimization Step Size for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability[pass1\
		]=
	Capacity Market Price for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability by Optimization Pass\
		[pass1]
	/ 2 ~~|
Capacity Market Optimization Step Size for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability[current pass\
		]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  Capacity Market Steps in Same Direction for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability\
		[preceeding pass]
	  > Steps Allowed in Same Direction Without Increasing Step Size,
	
	  Capacity Market Optimization Step Size for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability\
		[preceeding pass] * 1.5,
	
	  IF THEN ELSE(
	    Capacity Market Steps in Same Direction for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability\
		[preceeding pass]
	    > Steps Allowed in Same Direction With Declining Step Size,
	
	    Capacity Market Optimization Step Size for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability\
		[preceeding pass],
	
	    Capacity Market Optimization Step Size for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability\
		[preceeding pass]
	    / 2
	  )
	)
	~	$/(MW*day)
	~		|

Capacity Market Optimization Step Size for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability[pass1]=
	Capacity Market Price for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability by Optimization Pass[pass1\
		]
	/ 2 ~~|
Capacity Market Optimization Step Size for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability[current pass\
		]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  Capacity Market Steps in Same Direction for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability[preceeding pass\
		]
	  > Steps Allowed in Same Direction Without Increasing Step Size,
	
	  Capacity Market Optimization Step Size for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability[preceeding pass\
		] * 1.5,
	
	  IF THEN ELSE(
	    Capacity Market Steps in Same Direction for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability[preceeding pass\
		]
	    > Steps Allowed in Same Direction With Declining Step Size,
	
	    Capacity Market Optimization Step Size for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability[preceeding pass\
		],
	
	    Capacity Market Optimization Step Size for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability[preceeding pass\
		]
	    / 2
	  )
	)
	~	$/(MW*day)
	~		|

Capacity Market Price for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability Adjusted for Availability\
		[Electricity Source] :EXCEPT:   [Clean Dispatchable Electricity Source]=
	0 ~~|
Capacity Market Price for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability Adjusted for Availability\
		[Clean Dispatchable Electricity Source]=
	SUM(Capacity Market Price for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability by Optimization Pass\
		[last pass!]*Days per Year*One Day*Last Year Hourly Bid Electricity Capacity Factors for Clean Firm Reliability in Binding Hour by Plant Type
	[Clean Dispatchable Electricity Source])
	~	$/MW
	~		|

Capacity Market Price for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability by Optimization Pass\
		[pass1]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	
	  Time = INITIAL TIME, 
	  0, 
	  Initial Guess at Capacity Market Price
	 ) ~~|
Capacity Market Price for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability by Optimization Pass\
		[current pass]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  Capacity Market Price for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability by Optimization Pass\
		[preceeding pass] = 0,
	
	  0,
	
	  MAX(
	    IF THEN ELSE(
	      Net Electricity Clean Firm Demand Relative to Available Clean Firm Supply by Hour by Optimization Pass for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability under CES\
		[preceeding pass] > 0,
	  
	      Capacity Market Price for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability by Optimization Pass\
		[preceeding pass]
	      + Capacity Market Optimization Step Size for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability\
		[current pass],
	
	      Capacity Market Price for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability by Optimization Pass\
		[preceeding pass]
	      - Capacity Market Optimization Step Size for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability\
		[current pass]
	    ),
	
	    0
	  )
	)
	~	$/(MW*day)
	~		|

Capacity Market Price for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability Adjusted for Availability\
		[Electricity Source]=
	VMAX(Capacity Market Price for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability by Optimization Pass\
		[last pass!]*Hourly Bid Electricity Capacity Factors by Plant Type
	[peak day electricity timeslice!,Hour!,Electricity Source])
	~	$/(MW*day)
	~		|

Capacity Market Price for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability by Optimization Pass[pass1\
		]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	
	  Time = INITIAL TIME, 
	  0, 
	  Initial Guess at Capacity Market Price
	 ) ~~|
Capacity Market Price for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability by Optimization Pass[current pass\
		]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  Capacity Market Price for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability by Optimization Pass[preceeding pass\
		] = 0,
	
	  0,
	
	  MAX(
	    IF THEN ELSE(
	      Net Electricity Demand Relative to Available Supply in Binding Hour by Optimization Pass\
		[preceeding pass] > 0,
	  
	      Capacity Market Price for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability by Optimization Pass\
		[preceeding pass]
	      + Capacity Market Optimization Step Size for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability\
		[current pass],
	
	      Capacity Market Price for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability by Optimization Pass\
		[preceeding pass]
	      - Capacity Market Optimization Step Size for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability\
		[current pass]
	    ),
	
	    0
	  )
	)
	~	$/(MW*day)
	~		|

Capacity Market Steps in Negative Direction for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability\
		[pass1]=
	0 ~~|
Capacity Market Steps in Negative Direction for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability\
		[current pass]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  Net Electricity Clean Firm Demand Relative to Available Clean Firm Supply by Hour by Optimization Pass for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability under CES\
		[preceeding pass]
	  <0,
	Capacity Market Steps in Negative Direction for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability\
		[preceeding pass] + 1,
	
	  0
	)
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Capacity Market Steps in Negative Direction for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability[pass1\
		]=
	0 ~~|
Capacity Market Steps in Negative Direction for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability[current pass\
		]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  Net Electricity Demand Relative to Available Supply in Binding Hour by Optimization Pass\
		[preceeding pass]
	  <0,
	Capacity Market Steps in Negative Direction for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability[preceeding pass
	] + 1,
	
	  0
	)
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Capacity Market Steps in Positive Direction for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability\
		[pass1]=
	0 ~~|
Capacity Market Steps in Positive Direction for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability\
		[current pass]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  Net Electricity Clean Firm Demand Relative to Available Clean Firm Supply by Hour by Optimization Pass for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability under CES\
		[preceeding pass]
	  >=0,
	
	  Capacity Market Steps in Positive Direction for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability\
		[preceeding pass] + 1,
	
	  0
	)
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Capacity Market Steps in Positive Direction for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability[pass1\
		]=
	0 ~~|
Capacity Market Steps in Positive Direction for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability[current pass\
		]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	Net Electricity Demand Relative to Available Supply in Binding Hour by Optimization Pass\
		[preceeding pass]
	  >=0,
	
	  Capacity Market Steps in Positive Direction for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability[\
		preceeding pass] + 1,
	
	  0
	)
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Capacity Market Steps in Same Direction for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability[Optimization Pass\
		]=
	MAX(
	  Capacity Market Steps in Positive Direction for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability\
		[Optimization Pass],
	  Capacity Market Steps in Negative Direction for Seasonal Clean Dispatchable Reliability\
		[Optimization Pass]
	)
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Capacity Market Steps in Same Direction for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability[Optimization Pass\
		]=
	MAX(
	  Capacity Market Steps in Positive Direction for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability[\
		Optimization Pass],
	  Capacity Market Steps in Negative Direction for Seasonal Dispatchable Reliability[\
		Optimization Pass]
	)
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Capacity Remaining to Retire After Vintage[Electricity Source,first modeled vintage]=
	(
	  Retiring Generation Capacity[Electricity Source]
	  + Decrease in Capacity from CCUS Retrofits[Electricity Source]
	)
	- 
	
	SUM(Capacity Retirements by Vintage[Electricity Source,first modeled vintage!]) * One Year\
		 ~~|
Capacity Remaining to Retire After Vintage[Electricity Source,current modeled vintages\
		]=
	Capacity Remaining to Retire After Vintage[Electricity Source,preceding modeled vintages\
		]
	- Capacity Retirements by Vintage[Electricity Source,current modeled vintages] * One Year
	~	MW
	~		|

Capacity Retirements Based on Economic Lifetime[Electricity Source,Modeled Vintage]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  (Time-Modeled Vintage to Year Mapping[Modeled Vintage])=BGCL BAU Generation Capacity Lifetime\
		[Electricity Source],
	  1,
	  0
	)
	* Last Year Electricity Generation Capacity by Vintage[Electricity Source,Modeled Vintage\
		]
	*BUCLfCR Boolean Use Capacity Lifetimes for Capacity Retirements
	~	MW
	~		|

Capacity Retirements by Vintage[Electricity Source,first modeled vintage]=
	MIN(
	  SUM(Last Year Electricity Generation Capacity by Vintage[Electricity Source,first modeled vintage\
		!]),
	
	  (Retiring Generation Capacity[Electricity Source]+Decrease in Capacity from CCUS Retrofits\
		[Electricity Source])
	) / One Year ~~|
Capacity Retirements by Vintage[Electricity Source,current modeled vintages]=
	MIN(
	  Last Year Electricity Generation Capacity by Vintage[Electricity Source,current modeled vintages\
		],
	
	  Capacity Remaining to Retire After Vintage[Electricity Source,preceding modeled vintages\
		]
	) / One Year
	~	MW/Year
	~		|

Capacity Retirements from Selected Schedule[Electricity Source]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	    Boolean Use Non BAU Capacity Retirement Schedule This Year[Electricity Source] >\
		 0,
	
	    CRbQ Capacity Retirements before Quantization[Electricity Source],
	
	    BCRbQ BAU Capacity Retirements before Quantization[Electricity Source]
	)
	~	MW
	~		|

Capital Cost of Epqt to Sequester One Ton of Industry CO2 per Year[Industry Category,\
		Emissions Type]=
	Last Year Capital Cost of Eqpt to Sequester One Ton of Industry CO2 per Year[Industry Category\
		,Emissions Type]
	* This Year CCS Cost as Fraction of Last Year CCS Cost
	* (1 - RnD CCS Capital Cost Perc Reduction This Year)
	~	$/metric ton CO2e/Year
	~		|

Capital Cost of Eqpt to Sequester One Ton of Hydrogen Sector CO2 per Year=
	Last Year Capital Cost of Eqpt to Sequester One Ton of Hydrogen Sector CO2 per Year
	* This Year CCS Cost as Fraction of Last Year CCS Cost
	* (1 - RnD CCS Capital Cost Perc Reduction This Year)
	~	$/metric ton CO2e/Year
	~		|

Capital Recovery Factor by Industry Fuel and Process[Industry Category,Industrial Fuel\
		,Industrial Process]=
	ZIDZ(
	  Cost of Capital by Industry Fuel and Process[Industry Category,Industrial Fuel,Industrial Process\
		]
	  * (1 + Cost of Capital by Industry Fuel and Process[Industry Category,Industrial Fuel\
		,Industrial Process])^(RPfFISCC Repayment Period for Financed Industry Sector Capital Costs\
		[Industrial Process]
	 / One Year)
	,
	
	  (1 + Cost of Capital by Industry Fuel and Process[Industry Category,Industrial Fuel\
		,Industrial Process])^(RPfFISCC Repayment Period for Financed Industry Sector Capital Costs\
		[Industrial Process]
	 / One Year)
	  - 1
	)
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Capital Recovery Factor for Buildings Sector Investments=
	ZIDZ(
	  BCoESC BAU Cost of Electricity Sector Capital for Distributed Solar
	  * (1 + BCoESC BAU Cost of Electricity Sector Capital for Distributed Solar)^(RPfFBSCC Repayment Period for Financed Buildings Sector Capital Costs
	 / One Year)
	,
	
	  (1 + BCoESC BAU Cost of Electricity Sector Capital for Distributed Solar)^(RPfFBSCC Repayment Period for Financed Buildings Sector Capital Costs
	 / One Year)
	  - 1
	)
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Capital Recovery Factor for Financed Waste Heat Recovery Equipment[Industry Category]\
		=
	ZIDZ(
	  BCoISC Financing Interest Rate by Industry[Industry Category]
	  * (1 + BCoISC Financing Interest Rate by Industry[Industry Category])^(RPfFISCC Repayment Period for Financed Industry Sector Capital Costs
	[other processes]
	 / One Year)
	,
	
	  (1 + BCoISC Financing Interest Rate by Industry[Industry Category])^(RPfFISCC Repayment Period for Financed Industry Sector Capital Costs
	[other processes]
	 / One Year)
	  - 1
	)
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Capital Recovery Factor for Hydrogen Producers=
	ZIDZ(
	  BCoHSC BAU Cost of Hydrogen Sector Capital
	  * (1 + BCoHSC BAU Cost of Hydrogen Sector Capital)^(RPfFHSCC Repayment Period for Financed Hydrogen Sector Capital Costs
	 / One Year)
	,
	
	  (1 + BCoHSC BAU Cost of Hydrogen Sector Capital)^(RPfFHSCC Repayment Period for Financed Hydrogen Sector Capital Costs
	 / One Year)
	  - 1
	)
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Capital Recovery Factor for Other Electricity Sector Investments=
	ZIDZ(
	  BCoESC BAU Cost of Electricity Sector Capital for Other Investments
	  * (1 + BCoESC BAU Cost of Electricity Sector Capital for Other Investments)^(RPfFESCC Repayment Period for Financed Electricity Sector Capital Costs
	 / One Year)
	,
	
	  (1 + BCoESC BAU Cost of Electricity Sector Capital for Other Investments)^(RPfFESCC Repayment Period for Financed Electricity Sector Capital Costs
	 / One Year)
	  - 1
	)
	~	Dmnl
	~	The capital recovery factor (CRF) is the amount of repayment paid in each \
		year as a share of the amount of upfront money borrowed/financed.  Details \
		and formula at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capital_recovery_factor
	|

Capital Recovery Factor for Power Plants[Electricity Source]=
	ZIDZ(
	  Cost of Electricity Sector Capital for Power Plants[Electricity Source]
	  * (1 + Cost of Electricity Sector Capital for Power Plants[Electricity Source])^(RPfFESCC Repayment Period for Financed Electricity Sector Capital Costs
	 / One Year)
	,
	
	  (1 + Cost of Electricity Sector Capital for Power Plants[Electricity Source])^(RPfFESCC Repayment Period for Financed Electricity Sector Capital Costs
	 / One Year)
	  - 1
	)
	~	Dmnl
	~	The capital recovery factor (CRF) is the amount of repayment paid in each \
		year as a share of the amount of upfront money borrowed/financed.  Details \
		and formula at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capital_recovery_factor
	|

Capital Recovery Factor for Subisides per Unit Electricity Output[Electricity Source]\
		=
	ZIDZ(
	  Cost of Electricity Sector Capital for Power Plants[Electricity Source]
	  * (1 + Cost of Electricity Sector Capital for Power Plants[Electricity Source])^(BCS Duration of Subsidies for Carbon Sequestration
	 / One Year)
	,
	
	  (1 + Cost of Electricity Sector Capital for Power Plants[Electricity Source])^(BCS Duration of Subsidies for Carbon Sequestration
	 / One Year)
	  - 1
	)
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Capital Recovery Factor for Subsidies per Unit Electricity Output[Electricity Source]\
		=
	ZIDZ(
	  Cost of Electricity Sector Capital for Power Plants[Electricity Source]
	  * (1 + Cost of Electricity Sector Capital for Power Plants[Electricity Source])^(BS Duration of Subsidies per Unit Electricity Output\
		[Electricity Source]
	 / One Year)
	,
	
	  (1 + Cost of Electricity Sector Capital for Power Plants[Electricity Source])^(BS Duration of Subsidies per Unit Electricity Output\
		[Electricity Source]
	  / One Year)
	  - 1
	)
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

CApULAbIFM CO2 Abated per Unit Land Area by Improved Forest Management=
	GET DIRECT CONSTANTS(
	   'InputData/land/CApULAbIFM/CApULAbIFM.csv',
	   ',',
	   'B2*'
	)
	~	g pollutant/acre
	~		|

Carbon Free Energy after LCFS[Vehicle Type,Cargo Type,Vehicle Technology,Transportation Fuel\
		]=
	Carbon Free Energy in Absence of LCFS by Vehicle Type[Vehicle Type,Cargo Type,Vehicle Technology\
		,Transportation Fuel]
	+ Additional Carbon Free Energy Allocated by Fuel and Technology[Vehicle Type,Cargo Type\
		,Vehicle Technology,Transportation Fuel]
	~	BTU
	~		|

Carbon Free Energy in Absence of LCFS by Vehicle Type[Vehicle Type,Cargo Type,Vehicle Technology\
		,Transportation Fuel]=
	Fuel that would be Used by Regulated Vehicle Types in Absence of LCFS with Elec Eff Adj\
		[Vehicle Type,Cargo Type,Vehicle Technology,Transportation Fuel]
	* (1 - Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[Transportation Fuel])
	~	BTU
	~		|

Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[electricity tf]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  CIRbTF Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[electricity tf] <> -1,
	
	  CIRbTF Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[electricity tf],
	
	  MIN(
	    Transportation Fuel Pollutant Emissions Intensities This Year[LDVs,CO2,electricity tf\
		]
	    / Transportation Fuel Pollutant Emissions Intensities This Year[LDVs,CO2,petroleum gasoline tf\
		],
	
	    1
	  )
	) ~~|
Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[natural gas tf]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  CIRbTF Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[natural gas tf] <> -1,
	
	  CIRbTF Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[natural gas tf],
	
	  MIN(
	    Transportation Fuel Pollutant Emissions Intensities This Year[HDVs,CO2,natural gas tf\
		]
	    / Transportation Fuel Pollutant Emissions Intensities This Year[HDVs,CO2,petroleum diesel tf\
		],
	
	    1
	  )
	) ~~|
Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[petroleum gasoline tf]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  CIRbTF Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[petroleum gasoline tf] <> -1\
		,
	
	  CIRbTF Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[petroleum gasoline tf],
	
	  1
	) ~~|
Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[petroleum diesel tf]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  CIRbTF Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[petroleum diesel tf] <> -1,
	
	  CIRbTF Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[petroleum diesel tf],
	
	  1
	) ~~|
Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[biofuel gasoline tf]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  CIRbTF Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[biofuel gasoline tf] <> -1,
	
	  CIRbTF Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[biofuel gasoline tf],
	
	  MIN(
	    Transportation Fuel Pollutant Emissions Intensities This Year[LDVs,CO2,biofuel gasoline tf\
		]
	    / Transportation Fuel Pollutant Emissions Intensities This Year[LDVs,CO2,petroleum gasoline tf\
		],
	
	    1
	  )
	) ~~|
Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[biofuel diesel tf]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  CIRbTF Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[biofuel diesel tf] <> -1,
	
	  CIRbTF Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[biofuel diesel tf],
	
	  MIN(
	    Transportation Fuel Pollutant Emissions Intensities This Year[HDVs,CO2,biofuel diesel tf\
		]
	    / Transportation Fuel Pollutant Emissions Intensities This Year[HDVs,CO2,petroleum diesel tf\
		],
	
	    1
	  )
	) ~~|
Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[jet fuel tf]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  CIRbTF Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[jet fuel tf] <> -1,
	
	  CIRbTF Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[jet fuel tf],
	
	  1
	) ~~|
Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[heavy or residual fuel oil tf]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  CIRbTF Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[heavy or residual fuel oil tf\
		] <> -1,
	
	  CIRbTF Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[heavy or residual fuel oil tf\
		],
	
	  MIN(
	    Transportation Fuel Pollutant Emissions Intensities This Year[ships,CO2,heavy or residual fuel oil tf\
		]
	    / Transportation Fuel Pollutant Emissions Intensities This Year[ships,CO2,petroleum diesel tf\
		],
	
	    1
	  )
	) ~~|
Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[LPG propane or butane tf]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  CIRbTF Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[LPG propane or butane tf] <>\
		 -1,
	
	  CIRbTF Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[LPG propane or butane tf],
	
	  MIN(
	    Transportation Fuel Pollutant Emissions Intensities This Year[LDVs,CO2,LPG propane or butane tf\
		]
	    / Transportation Fuel Pollutant Emissions Intensities This Year[LDVs,CO2,petroleum gasoline tf\
		],
	
	    1
	  )
	) ~~|
Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[hydrogen tf]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  CIRbTF Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[hydrogen tf] <> -1,
	
	  CIRbTF Carbon Intensity Ratios by Transportation Fuel[hydrogen tf],
	
	  MIN(
	    Transportation Fuel Pollutant Emissions Intensities This Year[LDVs,CO2,hydrogen tf\
		]
	    / Transportation Fuel Pollutant Emissions Intensities This Year[LDVs,CO2,petroleum gasoline tf\
		],
	
	    1
	  )
	)
	~	Dmnl
	~	Reference fuels (petroleum gasoline, petroleum diesel, and jet fuel) have \
		carbon intensity ratios of 1.  When a non-reference transportation fuel \
		can be used by more than one type of vehicle (such as electricity, which \
		can be used by electric cars (LDVs) and electric buses (HDVs)), we \
		determine the carbon intensity ratio of that fuel based on the vehicle \
		type that most commonly uses that fuel (LDVs, in the case of electricity).
	|

Carbon Price Credit per MWh[Electricity Source]=
	Metric Tons CO2 Stored per MWh[Electricity Source]*Carbon Tax Rate[electricity sector\
		]
	~	$/(MW*hr)
	~		|

Carbon Price in Future Years[Sectors,Future Year]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  Dimensionless Time >= FYIbFP First Year Impacted by Future Policies,
	
	  Constant Reading of BCTR[Sectors,Future Year]
	  + Additional Carbon Price by Year from Policy Setting[Sectors,Future Year],
	
	  Constant Reading of BCTR[Sectors,Future Year]
	)
	~	$/metric ton CO2e
	~		|

Carbon Tax Effects on Expenditures by Nonenergy Industries[Industry Category]=
	SUM(Cost of Process Emissions Policies due to Carbon Tax[Industry Category,Industry Process Emissions Policy
	!])
	+ Change in Carbon Tax on Process Emissions by Industry[Industry Category]
	+ Change in Carbon Tax Levied on Industrial Fuels[Industry Category]
	
	- Change in Industry Sector Carbon Tax Rebate due to CCS[Industry Category]
	~	$
	~		|

Carbon Tax Effects on Expenditures by Nonenergy Industries As Share of Nonenergy Industry Output\
		[Industry Category]=
	ZIDZ(
	
	  IF THEN ELSE( 
	
	    Is Carbon Tax Border Adjustment Disabled > 0,
	
	    0, 
	
	    Carbon Tax Effects on Expenditures by Nonenergy Industries Passed Through to Buyers\
		[Industry Category]
	
	  ),
	
	  Last Year Output by ISIC Code[Industry Category ISIC Code]
	
	)
	* Fraction of Industry Covered by Carbon Tax Border Adjustment[Industry Category]
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Carbon Tax Effects on Expenditures by Nonenergy Industries Passed Through to Buyers[Industry Category\
		]=
	Carbon Tax Effects on Expenditures by Nonenergy Industries[Industry Category]
	* SoCiIEPTtB Share of Change in Industry Expenses Passed Through to Buyers[Industry Category\
		]
	~	$
	~		|

Carbon Tax Levied on Industrial Fuels[Industry Category]=
	SUM(
	  Industrial Fuel Use for Energy Purposes[Industrial Fuel!,Industry Category]
	  * Industrial Fuel Carbon Tax Amount per Unit Energy[Industry Category,Industrial Fuel\
		!]
	)
	~	$
	~		|

Carbon Tax on Process Emissions by Industry[Industry Category]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  Does Carbon Tax Exempt Process Emissions This Year[Industry Category] > 0,
	
	  0,
	
	  QUANTUM(
	
	    SUM(Process Emissions in CO2e in Metric Tons[Industry Category,Pollutant!]
	    * Carbon Tax Rate[industry sector]
	    * Fraction of Industry Category Subject to Carbon Tax[Industry Category]
	    * Industry Pollutants Taxed by Carbon Pricing[Industry Category,Pollutant!]
	    ),
	
	    QSfCF Quantization Size for Cash Flows
	  )
	)
	~	$
	~		|

Carbon Tax per Unit Industrial Output[Industry Category]=
	Carbon Tax Rate[industry sector]
	* Industrial Emissions per Unit Output[Industry Category]
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Carbon Tax Rate[Sectors]=
	BCTR BAU Carbon Tax Rate[Sectors]
	+ Additional Carbon Tax Rate This Year[Sectors]
	~	$/metric ton CO2e
	~		|

Carbon Tax Rebate on Exported Nonenergy Products[Industry Category]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  Is Carbon Tax Border Adjustment Disabled = 0,
	
	  Exports of Nonenergy Products[Industry Category]
	  * Carbon Tax per Unit Industrial Output[Industry Category],
	
	  0
	)
	* BRCToEP Boolean Rebate Carbon Tax on Exported Products
	* Fraction of Industry Covered by Carbon Tax Border Adjustment[Industry Category]
	~	$
	~		|

Cargo Dist Increases due to Mode Shifting[Target Vehicle Type,Cargo Type]=
	SUM(
	  Cargo Dist Transported after Macroeconomic Feedbacks[Vehicle Type!,Cargo Type]
	  * Percent of Travel Demand Shifted to Other Modes or Eliminated This Year[Cargo Type\
		,Vehicle Type!]
	  * RTMF Recipient Transportation Mode Fractions[Cargo Type,Vehicle Type!,Target Vehicle Type\
		]
	)
	~	thing*miles
	~		|

Cargo Dist Reductions due to Mode Shifting[Vehicle Type,Cargo Type]=
	Cargo Dist Transported after Macroeconomic Feedbacks[Vehicle Type,Cargo Type]
	* Percent of Travel Demand Shifted to Other Modes or Eliminated This Year[Cargo Type\
		,Vehicle Type]
	~	thing*miles
	~		|

Cargo Dist Transported after Macroeconomic Feedbacks[Vehicle Type,Cargo Type]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  BDMFL Boolean Disable Macroeconomic Feedback Loops > 0,
	
	  BAU Cargo Dist Transported[Vehicle Type,Cargo Type],
	
	  MAX(
	    0,
	
	    BAU Cargo Dist Transported[Vehicle Type,Cargo Type]
	    * (1 + Percent Change in Transport Demand due to Macroeconomic Feedbacks by Cargo Type\
		[Cargo Type])
	  )
	)
	~	thing*miles
	~		|

Cargo Dist Transported after Mode Shifting[Vehicle Type,Cargo Type]=
	Cargo Dist Transported after Macroeconomic Feedbacks[Vehicle Type,Cargo Type]
	- Cargo Dist Reductions due to Mode Shifting[Vehicle Type,Cargo Type]
	+ Cargo Dist Increases due to Mode Shifting[Vehicle Type,Cargo Type]
	~	thing*miles
	~		|

Cargo Dist Transported Allocated by Last Year Vehicle Technologies[Vehicle Type,Cargo Type\
		,Vehicle Technology]=
	Cargo Dist Transported after Mode Shifting[Vehicle Type,Cargo Type]
	* (1 + Perc Change in Sectoral Energy Use due to Exogenous GDP Adjustment[transportation sector\
		])
	
	* ZIDZ(
	    Last Year Vehicles[Vehicle Type,Cargo Type,Vehicle Technology],
	    SUM(Last Year Vehicles[Vehicle Type,Cargo Type,Vehicle Technology!])
	  )
	
	* (1 + Perc Change in Avg Annual Dist Traveled by Vehicle Type[Vehicle Type,Cargo Type\
		,Vehicle Technology])
	~	thing*miles
	~		|

Cargo Dist Transported by Vehicle Technology[Vehicle Type,Cargo Type,Vehicle Technology\
		]=
	SUM(Cargo Dist Transported Allocated by Last Year Vehicle Technologies[Vehicle Type,\
		Cargo Type,Vehicle Technology!])
	* ZIDZ(
	    Vehicles[Vehicle Type,Cargo Type,Vehicle Technology],
	    SUM(Vehicles[Vehicle Type,Cargo Type,Vehicle Technology!])
	  )
	~	thing*miles
	~		|

Cargo Type:
	passenger,
	freight
	~	
	~		|

Cash Flow Change for Fuel Industry from Industry Fuel Use[Industry Category,Industrial Fuel\
		]=
	Change in Amount Spent on Industry Fuels[Industry Category,Industrial Fuel]
	- Change in Taxes Paid on Industry Fuels[Industry Category,Industrial Fuel]
	~	$
	~		|

Cash Flow Entity:
	government,
	nonenergy industries,
	labor and consumers,
	foreign entities,
	electricity suppliers,
	coal suppliers,
	natural gas and petroleum suppliers,
	biomass and biofuel suppliers,
	other energy suppliers
	~	
	~		|

cash flow entity excluding energy suppliers:
	government,
	nonenergy industries,
	labor and consumers,
	foreign entities
	~	
	~		|

