	   'InputData/elec/DCpUC/DCpUC.csv',
	   ',',
	   'B2*'
	)
	~	$/MW
	~		|

Decline in Grid Battery Cost=
	Difference Between This Year and First Year Battery Cost
	/ RPfFESCC Repayment Period for Financed Electricity Sector Capital Costs
	*ESTRTE Grid Battery Round Trip Efficiency
	*One Year
	~	$/(MW*hour)
	~		|

Decommissioning Costs=
	SUM(Retiring Generation Capacity[Electricity Source!]*DCpUC Decommissioning Cost per Unit Capacity\
		[Electricity Source!]
	)
	~	$
	~		|

Decrease in Capacity from CCUS Retrofits[Electricity Source] :EXCEPT: [hard coal es],\
		[natural gas combined cycle es],[biomass es],[lignite es]=
	0 ~~|
Decrease in Capacity from CCUS Retrofits[hard coal es]=
	Retrofit Capacity after Quantization[hard coal w CCS es] ~~|
Decrease in Capacity from CCUS Retrofits[natural gas combined cycle es]=
	Retrofit Capacity after Quantization[natural gas combined cycle w CCS es] ~~|
Decrease in Capacity from CCUS Retrofits[biomass es]=
	Retrofit Capacity after Quantization[biomass w CCS es] ~~|
Decrease in Capacity from CCUS Retrofits[lignite es]=
	Retrofit Capacity after Quantization[lignite w CCS es]
	~	MW
	~		|

Decrease in Capacity from Mandated CCUS Retrofits[Electricity Source] :EXCEPT:     [hard coal es\
		],[natural gas combined cycle es],[biomass es],[lignite es]=
	0 ~~|
Decrease in Capacity from Mandated CCUS Retrofits[hard coal es]=
	New Policy Mandated Retrofits[hard coal w CCS es] ~~|
Decrease in Capacity from Mandated CCUS Retrofits[natural gas combined cycle es]=
	New Policy Mandated Retrofits[natural gas combined cycle w CCS es] ~~|
Decrease in Capacity from Mandated CCUS Retrofits[biomass es]=
	New Policy Mandated Retrofits[biomass w CCS es] ~~|
Decrease in Capacity from Mandated CCUS Retrofits[lignite es]=
	New Policy Mandated Retrofits[lignite w CCS es]
	~	MW
	~		|

Decrease in Demand by Hour for Diurnal Net Peak Load Reduction and RPS Compliance[Electricity Timeslice\
		,Hour]=
	Decrease in Demand by Hour for Diurnal Net Peak Load Reduction excluding Hybrid Batteries\
		[Electricity Timeslice,Hour]
	~	MW*hr
	~		|

Decrease in Demand by Hour for Diurnal Net Peak Load Reduction excluding Hybrid Batteries\
		[Electricity Timeslice,Hour]=
	Shortfall in Electricity vs Daily Average by Hour after Seasonal Net Peak Load Reduction\
		[Electricity Timeslice,Hour]
	* MIN(
	    1,
	
	    ZIDZ(
	      SUM(Increase in Demand by Hour for Diurnal Net Peak Load Reduction excluding Hybrid Batteries\
		[Electricity Timeslice
	,Hour!])
	        * Weighted Average Round Trip Efficiency for Diurnal Shifting Excluding Hybrid Batteries\
		[Electricity Timeslice]
	      + Maximum Daily Quantity of Electricity Reduced by Demand Response Programs for Net Peak Load Reduction\
		[Electricity Timeslice
	],
	
	      SUM(Shortfall in Electricity vs Daily Average by Hour after Seasonal Net Peak Load Reduction\
		[Electricity Timeslice
	,Hour!])
	    )
	  )
	~	MW*hr
	~		|

Decrease in Demand by Hour for Seasonal Net Peak Load Reduction[Electricity Timeslice\
		,Hour]=
	Daily Decrease in Demand for Seasonal Net Peak Load Reduction[Electricity Timeslice]
	* ZIDZ(
	    Shortfall in Potential Output from Surviving Capacity vs Annual Average by Hour[\
		Electricity Timeslice,Hour],
	    SUM(Shortfall in Potential Output from Surviving Capacity vs Annual Average by Hour\
		[Electricity Timeslice,Hour!])
	  )
	~	MW*hr
	~		|

Decrease in Process Emissions at BAU Production Levels[Industry Category,Industry Process Emissions Policy\
		,Pollutant]=
	ZIDZ(
	  Decrease in Process Emissions at BAU Production Levels by Pollutant in CO2e[Industry Category\
		,Industry Process Emissions Policy
	,Pollutant],
	  GbPbT GWP by Pollutant by Timeframe[Pollutant,one hundred years]
	)
	~	g pollutant
	~	We use one-hundred year GWP values here (rather than the user-selected \
		20-year or 100-year GWP values) because we must use the same timeframe as \
		our PERAC source document when converting from CO2e to pollutant.
	|

Decrease in Process Emissions at BAU Production Levels by Pollutant in CO2e[Industry Category\
		,Industry Process Emissions Policy
,Pollutant] :EXCEPT: [agriculture and forestry 01T03,indst livestock measures,Pollutant\
		],[agriculture and forestry 01T03,indst tillage,Pollutant]=
	MAX(
	
	  This Year Decrease in Process Emissions by Policy and Industry[Industry Category,Industry Process Emissions Policy\
		,Pollutant],
	
	  -BAU Process Emissions in CO2e[Industry Category,Pollutant]
	  * Fraction of Process Emissions Reductions by Policy[Industry Category,Industry Process Emissions Policy\
		,Pollutant]
	) ~~|
Decrease in Process Emissions at BAU Production Levels by Pollutant in CO2e[agriculture and forestry 01T03\
		,indst livestock measures
,Pollutant]=
	MAX(
	  -BAU Process Emissions in CO2e[agriculture and forestry 01T03,Pollutant]
	    * Percent Reduction in Agriculture Process Emissions from Shifting to Nonanimal Products
	  + This Year Decrease in Process Emissions by Policy and Industry[agriculture and forestry 01T03\
		,indst livestock measures,Pollutant]
	    * (1 - Percent Reduction in Agriculture Process Emissions from Shifting to Nonanimal Products\
		),
	
	  -BAU Process Emissions in CO2e[agriculture and forestry 01T03,Pollutant]
	    * Fraction of Process Emissions Reductions by Policy[agriculture and forestry 01T03\
		,indst livestock measures,Pollutant]
	) ~~|
Decrease in Process Emissions at BAU Production Levels by Pollutant in CO2e[agriculture and forestry 01T03\
		,indst tillage,Pollutant]=
	This Year Decrease in Process Emissions by Policy and Industry[agriculture and forestry 01T03\
		,indst tillage,Pollutant]
	~	g CO2e
	~	The second term in the MAX() function is to ensure that reductions do not \
		exceed total process emissions (of a given pollutant for a given \
		industry), which can happen if BPEiC and PERAC use different data sources.  \
		The tillage policy can sequester CO2, so it is allowed to reduce emissions \
		by more than the amount specified in BPE.
	|

Decrease in Process Emissions due to Policies[Industry Category,Industry Process Emissions Policy\
		,Pollutant]=
	Decrease in Process Emissions at BAU Production Levels[Industry Category,Industry Process Emissions Policy\
		,Pollutant]
	* (1 + Percent Change in Production due to Policies[Industry Category])
	~	g pollutant
	~		|

Demand for CCS Not Already Existing or In Progress[Industry Category,Emissions Type]=
	MAX(
	  CCS Retrofit Capacity Desired[Industry Category,Emissions Type]
	  - Last Year Total Deployed and Under Construction CCS[Industry Category,Emissions Type\
		],
	
	  0
	)
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Demand Responsive Electricity Capacity for Electrolyzers=
	Hydrogen Production by Pathway[electrolysis]
	* HPPECbP Hydrogen Production Percent Excess Capacity by Pathway[electrolysis]
	/ EHPpUC Electrolyzer Hydrogen Production per Unit Capacity
	
	 + Hydrogen Production by Pathway[electrolysis with guaranteed clean electricity]
	  * HPPECbP Hydrogen Production Percent Excess Capacity by Pathway[electrolysis with guaranteed clean electricity\
		]
	  / EHPpUC Electrolyzer Hydrogen Production per Unit Capacity
	~	MW
	~		|

