Fraction of Imported Industrial Outputs Shifted to In Region Suppliers This Year[Industry Category\
		]=
	Fraction of Imported Industrial Outputs Shifted to In Region Suppliers[Industry Category\
		]
	* VECTOR ELM MAP(
	    Selected Policy Implementation Schedule[indst buy in region outputs X agriculture and forestry 01T03\
		],
	
	    (Industry Category-1)
	  )
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Fraction of Imports Shifted to In Region Suppliers After Import Substitution[Industry Category\
		]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	
	  Percent of Purchases of Domestically Produced Goods Shifted to Purchases of Imports\
		[Industry Category] > 0,
	
	  Fraction of Imported Industrial Outputs Shifted to In Region Suppliers This Year[Industry Category\
		],
	
	  MIN(
	    1,
	
	    ZIDZ(
	      Fraction of Imported Industrial Outputs Shifted to In Region Suppliers This Year\
		[Industry Category],
	      (1 + Percent of Purchases of Domestically Produced Goods Shifted to Purchases of Imports\
		[Industry Category])
	    )
	  )
	)
	~	Dmnl
	~	We only augment the setting of the "Buy In-Region Lever" from import \
		shifting when import shifting causes an increase in domestic production \
		and a decrease in imports (similar to the buy in-region lever's effects).  \
		When import substitution would go the other way (increasing imports), we \
		don't want to alter "Fraction of Imported Industrial Outputs Shifted to In \
		Region Suppliers This Year" because it should still reach 100% when the \
		lever is set to 100%, and we don't need to worry about the (common) case \
		where the Buy In-Region lever is not being used, because we just want to \
		stick with DLIM in that case, and "Fraction of Imported Industrial Outputs \
		Shifted to In Region Suppliers This Year" will be zero, so it would still \
		be zero even if divided by a nonzero number.
	|

