	) ~~|
Increase in Process CO2e by Policy and Industry[agriculture livestock measures]=
	-SUM(
	  Decrease in Process Emissions due to Policies[agriculture and forestry 01T03,indst livestock measures\
		,Pollutant!]
	  * GbPbT GWP by Pollutant by Timeframe[Pollutant!,one hundred years]
	) ~~|
Increase in Process CO2e by Policy and Industry[agriculture tillage]=
	-SUM(
	  Decrease in Process Emissions due to Policies[agriculture and forestry 01T03,indst tillage\
		,Pollutant!]
	  * GbPbT GWP by Pollutant by Timeframe[Pollutant!,one hundred years]
	) ~~|
Increase in Process CO2e by Policy and Industry[chemicals N2O abatement]=
	-SUM(
	  Decrease in Process Emissions due to Policies[chemicals 20,indst N2O abatement,Pollutant\
		!]
	  * GbPbT GWP by Pollutant by Timeframe[Pollutant!,one hundred years]
	) ~~|
Increase in Process CO2e by Policy and Industry[other metals inspct maint retrofit]=
	-SUM(
	  Decrease in Process Emissions due to Policies[other metals 242,indst f gas inspct maint retrofit\
		,Pollutant!]
	  * GbPbT GWP by Pollutant by Timeframe[Pollutant!,one hundred years]
	)
	~	g CO2e
	~	We use one-hundred year GWP values here (rather than the user-selected \
		20-year or 100-year GWP values) because we must use the same timeframe as \
		our source document which provides marginal abatement curves in units of \
		100-year GWP CO2e.  We later convert to cash flow (using marginal cost \
		definitions that assume 100-year GWP values), so we don't have to worry \
		about converting back to "g pollutant" and then to "g CO2e" at a \
		user-selected GWP timeframe.
	|

Incremental Amount Spent to Buy Electrified Building Components[Building Type,Building Component\
		]=
	SUM(
	  New Component Energy Use Shifted to Electricity[Building Type,Building Fuel!,Building Component\
		]
	  * ICpUEfEBE Incremental Cost per Unit Energy for Electrified Building Equipment[Building Type\
		,Building Component,Building Fuel!]
	)
	~	$
	~		|

Incremental Carbon Tax from Policy[Industry Category]=
