Output by ISIC Code by Year[ISIC Code]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	
	  BDMFL Boolean Disable Macroeconomic Feedback Loops > 0,
	
	  BAU Output by ISIC Code by Year[ISIC Code],
	
	  BAU Output by ISIC Code by Year[ISIC Code]
	  + Change in Domestic Output by ISIC Code[ISIC Code]
	)
	~	$
	~	Output by ISIC Code is used as the denominator for dividing passthrough \
		expenses.  The macroeconomic feedback loop here isn't increasing \
		production.  (That feedback is below.)  We only use the BDMFL control \
		setting here because the denominator is influenced by these feedbacks, so \
		this code is non-duplicative of the code below where BDMFL appears.
	|

