		electricity if])
	) ~~|
Percent of Nonenergy Industry Electricity Spending by ISIC Code[Fossil and Energy Utility ISIC Code\
		]=
	0
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Percent of Output by Nonenergy Industry ISIC Code[ISIC Code] :EXCEPT:  [Nonenergy Industry ISIC Code\
		]=
	0 ~~|
Percent of Output by Nonenergy Industry ISIC Code[Nonenergy Industry ISIC Code]=
	ZIDZ(
	  BAU Output by ISIC Code by Year[Nonenergy Industry ISIC Code],
	
	  SUM(BAU Output by ISIC Code by Year[Nonenergy Industry ISIC Code!])
	)
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Percent of Payroll Tax Allocation by ISIC Code[ISIC Code] :EXCEPT:  [Private Business ISIC Code\
		]=
	0 ~~|
Percent of Payroll Tax Allocation by ISIC Code[Private Business ISIC Code]=
	BAU Employee Compensation by ISIC Code by Year[Private Business ISIC Code]
	/ SUM(BAU Employee Compensation by ISIC Code by Year[Private Business ISIC Code!])
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Percent of Purchases of Domestically Produced Goods Shifted to Purchases of Imports[Industry Category\
		]=
	MIN(
	
	  1,
	
	  MAX(
	
	    ZIDZ(
	
	      -(1 - Domestic Content Share of Consumption Before Import Substitution by ISIC Code\
		[Industry Category ISIC Code]),
	
	      Domestic Content Share of Consumption Before Import Substitution by ISIC Code[\
		Industry Category ISIC Code]
	
	    ),
	
	    Portion of Change in Passthrough Expenses as Share of Nonenergy Industry Output Affecting Imports and Exports\
		[Industry Category]
	    * IESE Import Export Substitution Elasticities[Industry Category]
	  )
	)
	~	Dmnl
	~	The first argument in the MIN() function prevents more than 100% of the \
		domestically produced goods from being replaced by imports.  The first \
		argument in the MAX() function is for when the shift is negative (i.e., \
		from imports to domestically produced goods) and limits this shift so that \
		domestic content share cannot exceed 100%.  The second argument in the \
		MAX() function is the most important argument and is the one that is \
		responsible for caluclating the shift of domestically produced goods to \
		imports or vice versa when neither of the two limits mentioned above are \
		reached.
	|

Percent of Travel Demand Shifted to Other Modes or Eliminated[Cargo Type,Vehicle Type\
		]=
