	0,	{biofuel diesel - NOT USED}
	0,	{jet fuel or kerosene}
	0,	{heat - NOT USED}
	0,	{geothermal - NOT USED}
	0,	{lignite}
	0,	{crude oil}
	0,	{heavy or residual fuel oil}
	0,	{LPG propane or butane}
	0,	{municipal solid waste - NOT USED}
	0	{hydrogen - NOT USED}
	~	Dmnl [0,1]
	~	Electricity exports can be reduced using a different policy lever.  This \
		lever only allows you to reduce the export of fossil fuels.  This lever \
		will not work to reduce production of non-fossil fuels (those marked "NOT \
		USED" in the equation area of this variable).
	|

Percent Reduction in Fossil Fuel Exports This Year[All Fuels]=
	Percent Reduction in Fossil Fuel Exports[All Fuels]
	* VECTOR ELM MAP(
	    Selected Policy Implementation Schedule[indst reduce fossil fuel exports X electricity\
		],
	
	    (All Fuels-1)
	  )
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Percent Reduction in Nonenergy Nonagriculture Industry Product Demand[Industry Category\
		]=
	0,	{agriculture and forestry 01T03 - NOT USED}
	0,	{coal mining 05 - NOT USED}
	0,	{oil and gas extraction 06 - NOT USED}
	0,	{other mining and quarrying 07T08 - NOT USED}
	0,	{food beverage and tobacco 10T12 - NOT USED}
	0,	{textiles apparel and leather 13T15 - NOT USED}
	0,	{wood products 16 - NOT USED}
	0,	{pulp paper and printing 17T18 - NOT USED}
	0,	{refined petroleum and coke 19 - NOT USED}
	0,	{chemicals 20 - NOT USED}
	0,	{rubber and plastic products 22 - NOT USED}
	0,	{glass and glass products 231 - NOT USED}
	0,	{cement and other nonmetallic minerals 239}
	0,	{iron and steel 241}
	0,	{other metals 242 - NOT USED}
	0,	{metal products except machinery and vehicles 25 - NOT USED}
	0,	{computers and electronics 26 - NOT USED}
	0,	{appliances and electrical equipment 27 - NOT USED}
	0,	{other machinery 28 - NOT USED}
	0,	{road vehicles 29 - NOT USED}
	0,	{nonroad vehicles 30 - NOT USED}
	0,	{other manufacturing 31T33 - NOT USED}
	0,	{energy pipelines and gas processing 352T353 - NOT USED}
	0,	{water and waste 36T39 - NOT USED}
	0	{construction 41T43 - NOT USED}
	~	Dmnl [0,1]
	~	This policy represents a reduction in demand for non-energy, \
		non-agriculture industrial outputs.  It can be used to represent policies \
		such as (1) material-efficient building codes reducing the amount of \
		concrete or steel in buildings, (2) requirements for improved durability \
		or longevity of products, so they are replaced less often, (3) more re-use \
		of products or intensification of use, such as more car sharing instead of \
		people owning their own cars, (4) water efficiency or waste reduction, \
		etc.  Since energy demand is determined elsewhere in the model (through \
		the demand sectors and energy imports/exports), this policy cannot be used \
		on energy industries (natural gas and petroleum systems, coal mining).  As \
		the "chemicals" industry includes pharmaceuticals (grouped in the same \
		ISIC code), and financial impacts tend to be dominated by pharmaceuticals \
		(which are not amenable to material efficiency or re-use strategies), we \
		disallow the use of this policy on the "chemicals" industry, to avoid \
		erroneous financial impacts.  We similarly disallow the use of the policy \
		on the "other industries" category because it is too highly aggregated, \
		and actual material efficiency or re-use policies would only affect \
		certain industries within that category, so financial impacts would not be \
		right if applied to "other industries" as a whole.  As of 2.0.0, the \
		policy assumes demand from all purchasers (government,industry, consumers, \
		and foreign entities) is reduced proportionately to the amount of goods \
		they buy, and it does not have any implementation cost for the policy \
		itself, beyond the financial consequences of the demand reduction.  A \
		separate lever handles shifting agricultural demand from animal products \
		to non-animal products, which is the main potential mechanism of demand \
		reduction for agricultural products.
	|

Percent Reduction in Nonenergy Nonagriculture Industry Product Demand This Year[Industry Category\
		]=
	Percent Reduction in Nonenergy Nonagriculture Industry Product Demand[Industry Category\
		]
	* VECTOR ELM MAP(
	    Selected Policy Implementation Schedule[indst reduce nonenergy product demand X agriculture and forestry 01T03\
		],
	
	    (Industry Category-1)
	  )
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

