Percentage Reduction in Plant Downtime[Electricity Source]=
	0,	{hard coal}
	0,	{natural gas steam turbine}
	0,	{natural gas combined cycle}
	0,	{nuclear}
	0,	{hydro}
	0,	{onshore wind}
	0,	{solar PV}
	0,	{solar thermal}
	0,	{biomass}
	0,	{geothermal}
	0,	{petroleum}
	0,	{natural gas peaker}
	0,	{lignite}
	0,	{offshore wind}
	0,	{crude oil}
	0,	{heavy or residual fuel oil}
	0,	{municipal solid waste}
	0,      {hard coal w CCS}
	0,      {natural gas combined cycle w CCS}
	0,      {biomass w CCS}
	0,      {lignite w CCS}
	0,      {small modular reactor}
	0,      {hydrogen combustion turbine}
	0       {hydrogen combined cycle}
	~	Dmnl [0,0.6]
	~	This policy lever reduces total plant downtime, so a setting of 100% here \
		would indicate that the given plant type produces electricity at its \
		nameplate capacity in every hour of the year.  This is normally \
		unattainable because of necessary maintenance and repairs (for all plant \
		types) and because of a lack of sunlight, wind, or usable water at certain \
		times (for renewables).  Accordingly, take care to select a realistic \
		value for this policy- generally well short of 100%, especially for \
		renewables.
	|

Percentage Reduction in Plant Downtime This Year[Electricity Source]=
	Percentage Reduction in Plant Downtime[Electricity Source]
	* VECTOR ELM MAP(
	    Selected Policy Implementation Schedule[elec reduce plant downtime X hard coal es\
		],
	
	    (Electricity Source-1)
	  )
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

