	*Weighted Average Expected Capacity Factors by Hour without RAF[Electricity Source,Electricity Timeslice\
		,Hour]
	~	MW
	~		|

Potential Output from Industrial Equipment Installed During Model Run[Industry Category\
		,Industrial Process,Model Run Vintage]=
	Last Year Potential Output from Industrial Equipment Installed During Model Run[Industry Category\
		,Industrial Process,Model Run Vintage]
	+
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  This Year Model Run Vintage Flag[Model Run Vintage] = 1,
	  Output from New Industrial Equipment[Industry Category,Industrial Process],
	  0
	)
	- Potential Output from Retiring Industrial Equipment Installed During Model Run[Industry Category\
		,Industrial Process,Model Run Vintage] * One Year
	~	$
	~		|

Potential Output from Preexisting Industrial Equipment[Industry Category,Industrial Process\
		]=
	Last Year Potential Output from Preexisting Industrial Equipment[Industry Category,Industrial Process\
		]
	- Potential Output from Retiring Preexisting Industrial Equipment[Industry Category,\
		Industrial Process]
	~	$
	~		|

Potential Output from Retiring Industrial Equipment Installed During Model Run[Industry Category\
		,Industrial Process,Model Run Vintage]=
	Last Year Potential Output from Industrial Equipment Installed During Model Run[Industry Category\
		,Industrial Process,Model Run Vintage]
	* 
	Retiring Share of Industrial Equipment Desired Due to Equipment Age[Industrial Process\
		,Model Run Vintage]
	/ One Year
	~	$/Year
	~		|

Potential Output from Retiring Preexisting Industrial Equipment[Industry Category,Industrial Process\
		]=
	Initial Output by Industry Category and Process[Industry Category,Industrial Process\
		]
	* 
	This Year Fraction of Initial Industrial Equipment Retired[Industry Category,Industrial Process\
		]
	~	$
	~		|

Potential Output from Surviving Capacity by Hour[Electricity Timeslice,Hour]=
	SUM(
	  Surviving Electricity Generation Capacity before Economic Retirements[Electricity Source\
		!]
	  * Last Year Hourly Bid Electricity Capacity Factors by Plant Type[Electricity Timeslice\
		,Hour,Electricity Source!]
	)
	* One Hour
	~	MW*hr
	~		|

Power Plant Least Cost Dispatch Parameters as Vector[Electricity Source,ptype]=
	3 ~~|
Power Plant Least Cost Dispatch Parameters as Vector[Electricity Source,ppriority]=
	Dispatch or Opportunity Cost per Unit Electricity Output[Electricity Source] ~~|
Power Plant Least Cost Dispatch Parameters as Vector[Electricity Source,pwidth]=
	MAX(
	  ABS(MAX(NSDoDC Normalized Standard Deviation of Dispatch Costs[Electricity Source]\
		,0.01)
	    *(Dispatch or Opportunity Cost per Unit Electricity Output[Electricity Source]
	    + Variable Subsidies per Unit Elec Output[Electricity Source])
	  ),
	
	  0.01
	) ~~|
Power Plant Least Cost Dispatch Parameters as Vector[Electricity Source,pextra]=
	0
	~	$/(MW*hr)
	~	We require pwidth to be a minimum of 0.01 so that the dispatch allocations \
		do not result in an error due to 0 dispatch costs for some power plant \
		types
	|

PPEIdtICEaT Potential Percentage Eff Improvement due to Improved Contractor Edu and Training\
		[Building Component]=
	GET DIRECT CONSTANTS(
	   'InputData/bldgs/PPEIdtICEaT/PPEIdtICEaT.csv',
	   ',',
	   'B2*'
	)
	~	Dmnl
	~	This policy covers changes in air sealing, framing, and insulation, so it \
		applies to the "envelope" component.
	|

PPEIdtIL Potential Percentage Eff Improvement due to Improved Labeling[Building Component\
		,Building Type]=
	GET DIRECT CONSTANTS(
	   'InputData/bldgs/PPEIdtIL/PPEIdtIL.csv',
	   ',',
	   'B2'
	)
	~	Dmnl
	~	Improvement in efficiency of components selected by consumers due to \
		improved labeling.  The labeling influences consumers who are buying \
		appliances of all Quality levels, so it's represented as a simple \
		percentage increase in the efficiency of components sold (at all quality \
		levels).  (If Quality Levels are defined based on particular efficiency \
		thresholds, this may mean the number of square feet served by components \
		of a given quality level will not be accurate, but the end result in terms \
		of energy use will still be accurate.  It's just a question of the meaning \
		of the labels we give to each Quality level.)
	|

