Profitable Capacity for CCUS Retrofits[CCUS Electricity Source, Optimization Pass,RPS\
		]=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  Profitable Capacity as Share of Existing Capacity for Cost Effective CCUS Retrofits\
		[CCUS Electricity Source,Optimization Pass,RPS] = :NA:,
	
	  0,
	
	  Profitable Capacity as Share of Existing Capacity for Cost Effective CCUS Retrofits\
		[CCUS Electricity Source,Optimization Pass,RPS]
	  * MAX(
	      Minimum Buildable Capacity for Plants,
	      Last Year Electricity Generation Capacity[CCUS Electricity Source]
	    )
	) ~~|
Profitable Capacity for CCUS Retrofits[CCUS Electricity Source,Optimization Pass,CES]\
		=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  Profitable Capacity as Share of Existing Capacity for Cost Effective CCUS Retrofits\
		[CCUS Electricity Source,Optimization Pass,CES] = :NA:,
	
	  0,
	
	  Profitable Capacity as Share of Existing Capacity for Cost Effective CCUS Retrofits\
		[CCUS Electricity Source,Optimization Pass,CES]
	  * MAX(
	      Minimum Buildable Capacity for Plants,
	      Last Year Electricity Generation Capacity[CCUS Electricity Source]
	    )
	)
	~	MW
	~	If we do not test for :NA: (no number), then an out-of-bounds lookup in \
		the prior variable can produce a large random number here, which can throw \
		off the model. It may be better to output zero for an out-of-bounds lookup.
	|

Profitable Capacity for CCUS Retrofits without CES[CCUS Electricity Source]=
