Taxes Paid on Geoengineering Fuels[Industrial Fuel]=
	QUANTUM(
	  Geoengineering Sector Energy Use[Industrial Fuel]
	  * Geoengineering Fuel Total Tax or Subsidy Amount per Unit Energy[Industrial Fuel]\
		,
	
	  QSfCF Quantization Size for Cash Flows
	)
	~	$
	~	We use the tax amount per unit fuel from the cement industry as a model \
		for tax amounts per unit fuel from industry more generally, for use to \
		represent tax amount per unit fuel used by geoengineering.
	|

Taxes Paid on Industry Fuels[Industry Category,Industrial Fuel]=
	Industrial Fuel Use for Energy Purposes[Industrial Fuel,Industry Category]
	  * Industrial Fuel Total Tax or Subsidy Amount per Unit Energy[Industry Category,Industrial Fuel\
		]
	  * (1 - SoFCTiBoSFbI Share of Fuel Consumption That is Byproduct or Secondary Fuels by Industry\
		[Industry Category,Industrial Fuel])
	
	+ Industrial Fuel Use for Non Energy Purposes[Industry Category,Industrial Fuel]
	  * (
	      Industrial Fuel Total Tax or Subsidy Amount per Unit Energy[Industry Category,\
		Industrial Fuel]
	      - Industrial Fuel Carbon Tax Amount per Unit Energy[Industry Category,Industrial Fuel\
		]
	    )
	~	$
	~		|

TCCpUNEC Transmission Construction Cost per Unit New Electricity Capacity=
	GET DIRECT CONSTANTS(
	   'InputData/elec/TCCpUNEC/TCCpUNEC.csv',
	   ',',
	   'B2*'
	)
	~	$/MW
	~		|

Thermal Fuel Subsidies Paid[All Fuels,Sectors]=
	(Fuel Production[All Fuels]
	 * ZIDZ(
	     Total Energy Use by Sector[Sectors,All Fuels],
	
	     SUM(Total Energy Use by Sector[Sectors!,All Fuels])
	   )
	)
	* Subsidy for Thermal Fuels per Energy Unit Produced[All Fuels,Sectors]
	~	$
	~		|

This Year Battery Capacity Affecting Learning=
	Battery Storage Capacity Outside Modeled Region Affecting Learning
	+ Cumulative Battery Capacity Deployed
	~	MW*hr
	~		|

This Year Battery Capacity by Vehicle Type[Cargo Type,Vehicle Type,Vehicle Technology\
		]=
	Last Year Battery Capacity by Vehicle Type[Cargo Type,Vehicle Type,Vehicle Technology\
		]
	* (1 - AIiBCbVT Annual Improvement in Battery Capacity by Vehicle Type[Cargo Type,Vehicle Type\
		,Vehicle Technology])
	~	(kW*hr)/vehicle
	~		|

This Year Battery Cost as Fraction of Last Year Battery Cost=
	(1 - PDiBCpDoC Perc Decline in Battery Cost per Doubling of Capacity)
	^ ( LN(
	        This Year Battery Capacity Affecting Learning
	        / Last Year Battery Storage Affecting Learning
	      )
	    / LN(2)
	  )
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

This Year Battery Manufacturing Price After Subsidies=
	This Year Battery Manufacturing Price Before Subsidies
	- Subsidy for Vehicle Battery Production Passed Through to Consumers
	~	$/(kW*hr)
	~		|

This Year Battery Manufacturing Price Before Subsidies=
	IF THEN ELSE(BPP Battery Pack Price > 0,
	
	  BPP Battery Pack Price,
	
	  IF THEN ELSE(BPP Battery Pack Price With One Year Delay > 0,
	
	    BPP Battery Pack Price With One Year Delay
	     * This Year Battery Cost as Fraction of Last Year Battery Cost,
	
	    Last Year Battery Manufacturing Price
	     * This Year Battery Cost as Fraction of Last Year Battery Cost
	  )
	)
	~	$/(kW*hr)
	~		|

This Year Battery Portion of Vehicle Price[Cargo Type,Vehicle Type,Vehicle Technology\
		]=
	This Year Battery Capacity by Vehicle Type[Cargo Type,Vehicle Type,Vehicle Technology\
		]
	* This Year Battery Manufacturing Price After Subsidies
	~	$/vehicle
	~		|

This Year Battery Subsidy Passed Through to Consumers by Vehicle Type[Cargo Type,Vehicle Type\
		,Vehicle Technology]=
	This Year Battery Capacity by Vehicle Type[Cargo Type,Vehicle Type,Vehicle Technology\
		]
	* Subsidy for Vehicle Battery Production Passed Through to Consumers
	~	$/vehicle
	~		|

This Year Capacity Market Repayment=
	DEPRECIATE STRAIGHTLINE(
	
	  Total Capacity Market Costs
	  / One Year,
	 
	  Repayment Period for Capacity Market Charges,
	
	  1,
	
	  0
	)
	~	$/Year
	~		|

This Year CCS Cost as Fraction of Last Year CCS Cost=
	(1 - PDiCECpDoC Perc Decline in CCS Eqpt Cost per Doubling of Capacity)
	^ ( LN(
	        This Year CO2 Sequestered Affecting Learning
	        / Last Year CO2 Sequestered Affecting Learning
	      )
	    / LN(2)
	  )
	~	Dmnl
	~	In the event we have no CCS in the base year, we do not decline CCS costs \
		based on installed capacity, because we cannot calculate the doublings of \
		capacity from the base year.  Also, we disallow increases in CCS cost, \
		which could otherwise happen if CCS capacity declines in any year relative \
		to the prior year.
	|

This Year CCS Subsidies Paid[Electricity Source]=
	CCS Subsidies Paid per Unit Electricity Output for Newly Eligible CCS Capacity[Electricity Source\
		]
	
	+Last Year CCS Subsidies Paid per Unit Electricity Output for Newly Eligible CCS Capacity\
		[Electricity Source]
	
	- CCS Subsidy Payments per Unit Electricity Output Expiring After CCS Subsidy Duration Period\
		[Electricity Source]
	~	$
	~		|

This Year Change in Distributed Electricity Source Capacity[Building Type,Electricity Source\
		] :EXCEPT: [Building Type,solar PV es]=
	BAU This Year Increase in Distributed Electricity Source Capacity[Building Type,Electricity Source\
		] ~~|
This Year Change in Distributed Electricity Source Capacity[Building Type,solar PV es\
		]=
	BAU This Year Increase in Distributed Electricity Source Capacity[Building Type,solar PV es\
		]
	+ Distributed Solar Capacity Caused by Policies This Year[Building Type] * One Year
	~	MW
	~		|

This Year Change in Hydrogen Produced by Pathway[Hydrogen Production Pathway]=
	Hydrogen Production by Pathway[Hydrogen Production Pathway]
	- Last Year Hydrogen Produced by Pathway[Hydrogen Production Pathway]
	~	BTU
	~		|

This Year CO2 Sequestered[electricity sector]=
	SUM(This Year Pollutants Sequestered by Electricity Sector[CO2,Electricity Source!])
	/ Grams per Metric Ton CO2e
	/ Grams Pollutant per Gram CO2e Unit Converter ~~|
This Year CO2 Sequestered[industry sector]=
	SUM(This Year Pollutants Sequestered by Industry Sector[Industry Category!,CO2,Emissions Type\
		!])
	/ Grams per Metric Ton CO2e
	/ Grams Pollutant per Gram CO2e Unit Converter ~~|
This Year CO2 Sequestered[district heat and hydrogen sector]=
	This Year Pollutants Sequestered by Hydrogen Sector[CO2]
	/ Grams per Metric Ton CO2e
	/ Grams Pollutant per Gram CO2e Unit Converter
	~	metric tons CO2e
	~		|

This Year CO2 Sequestered Affecting Learning=
	This Year CO2 Sequestered Outside Modeled Region Affecting Learning
	+ SUM(Last Year CO2 Sequestered[CCS Sectors!])
	~	metric tons CO2e
	~		|

This Year CO2 Sequestered Outside Modeled Region Affecting Learning=
	MAX(
	  0,
	
	  (BCSG BAU CO2 Sequestered Globally
	    - SUM(BAU Last Year CO2 Sequestered[CCS Sectors!]))
	  * FoTOMRAEL Fraction of Technology Outside Modeled Region Affecting Endogenous Learning
	)
	~	metric tons CO2e
	~		|

This Year Cumulative Policy Mandated Grid Battery Storage=
	Last Year Cumulative Policy Mandated Grid Battery Storage
	+ Policy Mandated Grid Battery Storage Additions
	~	MW*hour
	~		|

