This equipment is retired in two ways: 1) naturally by age, using retirement curves from input data; or 2) through an early retirement policy that allows users to define the share of preexisting equipment retired early. Input data defines what fuel types qualify for early retirement. 
12,645,0,3008,1391,184,47,8,7,0,4,-1,0,0,0,-1--1--1,255-255-128,|||0-0-0,0,0,0,0,0,0
The industrial equipment early retirement policy lever can be set up to retire only equipment powered by specific fuels, for example coal-powered boilers. When it is on, we need to adjust the historical vintage's fuel type shares to account for fuel type retirements.
