The model also allows the user to explicitly define retirement profiles for specific industries. In small regions, there may be a limited number of facilities of a certain type -- for example, one integrated steelmaking plant. Therefore, using a smooth retirement curve as defined in IESD might not reflect the quantized nature of retirements expected of this industry.
