We do not use a rate/flow structure for this variable because the payments of a PTC are dependent on the actual production of industrial heat, thus rely on output from a particular vintage in each year. Since we've already calculated output/fuel shares by vintage on the main pages; it saves computational time to use this structure rather than recalculating.
