Balancing BAU Fuel Consumption, Production, Imports, and Exports
12,578,0,-4299,822,364,42,8,135,0,4,-1,0,0,0,-1--1--1,255-255-128,|||0-0-0,0,0,0,0,0,0
For each fuel, BAU in-region consumption should equal BAU production plus BAU imports minus BAU exports.  BAU consumption data is summed from the various sectors, which have the data with high granularity particular to each sector.  We ensure the equation holds by calculating one of the three other terms (production, imports, or exports), with the term to be calculated specified by input data (since this can vary by fuel and by modeled region).
