10,88,Change in Transportation Fuel Taxes Paid,6,1770,75,30,8,130,0,3,-1,0,0,0,128-128-128,0-0-0,|||128-128-128,0,0,0,0,0,0
12,89,0,647,2056,277,57,8,135,0,4,-1,0,0,0,-1--1--1,255-255-128,|||0-0-0,0,0,0,0,0,0
Carbon taxes are levied upstream on fuel sales, before it is known whether a unit of fuel will be burned with or without CCS.  So the government must pay CCS providers back for the tax they already paid (capitalized into the cost of their fuels).  Also, CCS providers might sell their CCS services on a market for credits.  So carbon tax rebates are distinct rebate payments (which we classify as subsidies), not a reduction in tax.
